<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="prep-11-23">
  <title>Resources for 11/23</title>

  <objectives>
    <introduction>
      <p>For the content of this class, you will be expected to be able to do the following:</p>
    </introduction>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          Identify all <m>x</m>-intercepts of the graph of a polynomial expressed in factored form.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Use the factored form of a polynomial to determine how the graph of the function behaves around the <m>x</m>-intercepts of the graph of the polynomial (i.e. does the graph <q>touch</q> the <m>x</m>-axis or <q>cross</q> the <m>x</m>-axis).
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Given the graph of a polynomial function, derive a plausible formula for the function.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="video-activity-desmos-sliders-2">
    <title>Video &amp; Activities for Using Sliders in Desmos (Continued from Last Class)</title>
    <p>
      Below is a YouTube video on using <em>sliders</em> in Desmos to help us understand roots of polynomials. It is followed by a link to a set of activities that we will be working on in class. Please watch the video and do as many of the activities as you can before class.
    </p>

    <video youtube="38a__ucpIX0" />

    <example>
      <title>Exploring Polynomial Roots and Graphs (Not on Quiz)</title>
      <p>
        Plug the following functions into Desmos, making a slider for each coefficient (i.e. <m>a</m>, <m>b</m>, <m>c</m>, etc).  Play with different values of the coefficients to see the minimum and maximum number of <m>x</m>-intercepts of the function (i.e. values of <m>x</m> where the function has an output of 0).
      </p>
      <p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=ax+b</m>, <m>a \ne 0</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>f(x) = cx^2+dx+e</m>, <m>c \ne 0</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>f(x) = gx^3+hx^2+ix+j</m>, <m>g \ne 0</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>f(x) = kx^4+\ell x^3 + mx^2+nx+p</m>, <m>k \ne 0</m>
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </example>
    <p>
      Feel free to post any questions you have on the <url href="">FigJam board</url> for the next class.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="video-activity-poly-graph-roots">
    <title>Video &amp; Activities for Graphing Polynomials from Roots</title>
    <p>
      Below is a YouTube video on <em>using the roots of polynomials to sketch their graphs</em>. It is followed by a link to a set of activities that we will be working on in class. Please watch the video and do as many of the activities as you can before class.
    </p>

    <video youtube="HLI_l0cFgOY" />

    <example>
      <title>Graphing Polynomials from Roots</title>
      <p>
        Solve the following problems on the graphs of polynomial functions.
      </p>
      <p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              Let <m>f(x)=2x^2-5x+3</m>.  Factor <m>f</m> and use this to sketch a graph of <m>f</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
               Let <m>f(x)=-3(x-1)(x-3)(x-4)</m>.  Use the roots of <m>f</m> along with the coefficient <m>-3</m> to sketch the graph of <m>f</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Let <m>f(x) = k(x-a)(x-b)(x-c)(x-d)</m> with <m>a &lt; b &lt; c &lt; d</m> and <m>k &gt; 0</m>.  Sketch the graph of <m>f</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Give a possible formula for the function whose graph is the following.
            </p>
            <image width="60%">
            	<prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="poly-no-repeat-prep">
                <diagram dimensions="(300, 300)" margins="5">
                  <definition>f(x)=0.2*(x+1)*(x-3)*(x-5)</definition>
                  <coordinates bbox="(-3,-5,8,5)">
                    <axes xlabel="x" ylabel="y" hticks="(-4,1,7)" vticks="no" vlabels="no" hlabels="(-3,1,7)" />
                    <graph function="f" />
                    <graph function="g" domain="(-1,1)" />
                    <graph function="h" domain="(1,4)" />
                    <graph function="k" domain="(-4,-1)" stroke="green" />
                    <graph function="m" domain="(-1,1)" stroke="green" />
                    <graph function="n" domain="(1,4)" stroke="green" />
                  </coordinates>
                </diagram>
              </prefigure>
            </image>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </example>
    <p>
      Feel free to post any questions you have on the <url href="">FigJam board</url> for the next class.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection>
    <title>Optional Reading</title>
